- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and OCR error correction. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper uses a large dataset to perform dictionary-based error correction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper proposes a combination of three algorithms to detect and correct OCR errors. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possibility as the paper deals with scanned images and OCR. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention the use of deep learning techniques.
